A fact family is a group of math facts using the same numbers. 

In the case of addition/subtraction, you use three numbers and get four facts.

  For example, you can form a fact family using the three numbers 10, 2, and 12: 10 + 2 = 12, 2 + 10 = 12, 12 − 10 = 2, and 12 − 2 = 10. In this case we know that 10+9=19, is related to 9 + 10 = 19, 19 - 10 = 9 and 19 - 9 = 10. The answer here is 19 - 9 = 10.
